Megan Willis

Bio

I am a senior Data Science student at Simmons University, Boston, MA. I have a strong background in Mathematics, Computer Science, and Biostatistics, with minors in all three disciplines. My research interests are in causal inference, data visualization, and predictive modeling. I have strong programming backgrounds in R and Python, as well as familiarity with SQL, Java, and C++.
